frameDefinitions: This frame is concerned with nouns denoting a part or parts of a Whole entity .
A Suspect has been investigated and has a warrant issued for his or her arrest on certain Charges. '

An Agent has attempted to achieve a Goal, and the actual outcome of the Agent's action has been resolved, so that it either specifically matches the Agent's intent (e.g. success) or does not match it (e.g. failure).
This frame concerns transparent nouns that denote Instances of Types of entities or events.
This frame concerns an Evaluee being judged for its quality, i.e. how much it would probably be liked.
An Entity meets the pre-conditions for participating in an Event.
frameExamples: Kim forgot a large <t><fex name='Part'>part</fex></t> of the story.
He <t>pulled</t> <t>off</t> his April Fool's Day prank by the barest of margins .

The survey confirmed that management interference in team operations had increased , and <t><fex name='Instance'>instances</fex></t> of management decisions being taken without team consultation had also increased .
Conductor software gives us the hands-on <t>capability</t> to provide updates immediately
listRoleDefinitions: An undivided entity having all its <fen>Part</fen>s.
The <fen>Suspect</fen> is suspected of having committed a crime by the authorities who want the <fen>Suspect</fen> to enter the criminal process.
The <fen>Agent</fen> makes an attempt to achieve a <fen>Goal</fen>.
The <fen>Goal</fen> is what the <fen>Agent</fen> attempts to achieve.
A participant function in a particular event or in events of a particular kind.
This role identifies the <fen>Time</fen> when the attempt succeeds or fails.
The place where an attempt succeeds or fails.
A thing or episode of a certain <fen>Type</fen>.
The category of thing or event of which an <fen>Instance</fen> is picked out.
The <fen>Evaluee</fen> is being judged for its quality.
This role marks expressions that denote a scalar property of the <fen>Evaluee</fen> with respect to which the <fen>Evaluee</fen> is judged.
The <fen>Entity</fen> whose meeting or falling short of pre-conditions is assessed.
The <fen>Event</fen> that the <fen>Entity</fen> may participate in.
The time at which the <fen>Entity</fen> is capable of the <fen>Event</fen>.
listRoleExamples: Sergey had  <fex>half</fex> of the pizza for breakfast.
Sergey had  half <fex>of the pizza</fex> for breakfast.
If you don't succeed <fex>in your subterfuge</fex>, then report back for further orders.
Benedikt was successful <fex>as a master brewer of beer</fex>.
<fex>On the bridge</fex> he succeeded in putting the wig on the corpse.
I collected two <t>specimens</t> <fex>of this rare species</fex>.
The Beaujolais Nouveau is dazzling <fex>in freshness</fex>.
White House voices doubts about Aristide's ability <fex>to govern</fex>
